{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f0163e45-63b1-4f1a-8311-27cf55544076","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. MSTest v3 **dropped support** for two of your three target frameworks:\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped (minimum is `net6.0`) |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped (minimum is `net6.0`) |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for .NET (Core) targets. Both `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` are end-of-life and no longer supported.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to update your `TargetFrameworks` to replace those with a supported version (e.g., `net6.0` or `net8.0`), and also switch to the unified `MSTest` meta-package:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net8.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.*\" />\n```\n\nWould you like me to update the project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"37e0fae9-6138-49f4-ae4e-a413009c5bcf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Let me check what the compatibility requirements are for MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 (MSTest 3.x / `MSTest` meta-package or `MSTest.TestFramework` 3.x) requires:\n- .NET 6+ for .NET (Core) targets\n- .NET Framework 4.6.2+ for .NET Framework targets\n\nSo:\n- `net462` — .NET Framework 4.6.2 is supported ✅\n\n\n- `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` won't work with MSTest v3 since both are below the .NET 6 minimum requirement, and they're already out of support anyway.","outputTokens":533,"requestId":"702E:32FCC3:3E087B:48C1BE:69F2BFF7"},"id":"bbe36d9e-f1f0-4b60-9c80-3a6e4d9bd89c","timestamp":"2026-04-30T02:35:48.088Z","parentId":"2b51bc1c-4043-470c-b797-db88148c2607"}
